While the database file is reachable the generated column is MATERIALIZED, so SELECT * returns only the base column:
a
10
After the first open the classification is repaired, so SELECT * again returns only the base column:
a
10
Insert without a column list targets only the base column; SQLite computes the generated column:
a	b
5	6
10	11
Explicitly writing into the generated column is rejected:
Cannot insert column b, because it is MATERIALIZED column
